 â”‚ PHASE 4: JWT AUTHENTICATION (Stateless, token-based)                        â”‚
 â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜

   7. Create JwtService
      â””â”€ Handles JWT tokens:

         â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
         â”‚   generateToken(UserDetails)        â”‚
         â”‚                                     â”‚
         â”‚   HEADER:    {typ: "JWT", ... }       â”‚
         â”‚   PAYLOAD:  {username, roles, ...}  â”‚
         â”‚   SIGNATURE:  HMAC-SHA256(secret)    â”‚
         â”‚                                     â”‚
         â”‚   OUTPUT:  "eyJhbGc..." (3 parts)    â”‚
         â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜

         Methods:
         â”œâ”€ generateToken(userDetails) â†’ "eyJ..."
         â”œâ”€ extractUsername(token) â†’ username
         â”œâ”€ extractClaim(token, claims) â†’ specific data
         â”œâ”€ isTokenValid(token, userDetails) â†’ true/false
         â””â”€ isTokenExpired(token) â†’ true/false

   8. Create JwtAuthenticationFilter (Runs on EVERY request)

         Request Flow:
         â”œâ”€ Extract "Authorization:  Bearer eyJ..." header
         â”œâ”€ Extract token (remove "Bearer ")
         â”œâ”€ Validate token signature
         â”œâ”€ Check if expired
         â”œâ”€ Extract username from token
         â”œâ”€ Load UserDetails from database
         â”œâ”€ Create Authentication object
         â”œâ”€ Put in SecurityContext (Spring knows user is authenticated!)
         â””â”€ Continue to controller

         If invalid?  â†’ Skip, let SecurityConfig handle it

